No lie His expressions in one of the tracks “Charge” where he featured one of the R2bees singers Mugeez. According to the lad, “In Transit” describes the metamorphosis of his music journey and his hope for future achievements. In his words:
“It’s me thinking about where I’m coming from, acknowledging my growth, and getting closer to my goals; I went through the previous year investigating various sounds and sharpening my specialty – this venture is a record of that imaginative excursion, as well as my own excursion going through the various feelings of adoration, connections, and sentiment. ‘In Transit’ is a progress from where I was artistically, to where I am currently, and where I’m going. It’s me pondering what I’m accustomed to, recognizing my development, and drawing nearer to my objectives”. Not just that, the other five tracks confess the pace, elation, and sensation felt by the singer in love and romance. “I spent the past year exploring different sounds and honing my craft.” He called it an account of his “artistic journey” and “personal journey going through the different emotions of love, relationships, and romance”, Terri explained. Though quiet an album, each song dropped by Terri excels independently. Notwithstanding, he understands that he still has to fight restlessly to the top of the food chain hence, the significance of the album title.